cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image compression and image processing using deep convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves regression problems, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of neural networks for image processing and compression also falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves optimization of loss functions, which is a common topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural networks for image compression also falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
